f
\begin{align*} f'(a) &= \lim_{h\to 0}\frac{f(a+h)-f(a)}{h}\\  &= \lim_{h\to 0}\frac{ \bigl(3(a+h)^2 -4(a+h) + 1\bigr) - \bigl(3a^2-4a+1\bigr)}{h}\\ &=\lim_{h\to 0}\frac{\bigl( 3(a^2+2ah+h^2) - 4a-4h +1\bigr) - \bigl(3a^2-4a+1\bigr)}{h}\\ &=\lim_{h\to 0}\frac{3a^2 + 6ah + 3h^2 - 4a - 4h + 1 - 3a^2 + 4a - 1}{h}\\ &=\lim_{h\to 0}\frac{3h^2 + 6ah - 4h}{h}. \end{align*}
f(x)=3x^2-4x+1
f'(x)=3\times 2x-4=6x-4
f'(a)=6a-4
